description.narrative: UNICEF Jamaica’s strategic communication and advocacy continued to support the national COVID-19 response. With the massive impact of school closures – particularly on the most vulnerable – UNICEF led a strong call, in collaboration with partners, for resumption of face-to-face school. Building on our unique role in engaging children and addressing their mental health, UNICEF consulted with hundreds of students to “Reimagine Education” in the wake of the pandemic and promoted a new counselling helpline for children. Under the Spotlight Initiative, UNICEF led a powerful storytelling initiative and engaged influencers to generate attention and catalyze conversations around gender-based violence. ; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
